artwork.name: All these flowers for you XI
Mumbai under shower
artwork.description:
Rain, on hearing this word, the first thing that comes to mind is water, sad and cloudy environment, laziness, floods and to top it all the Mumbai’s rain.
            But the theme of my paintings are based on this rain. In contrast to what is said above, my paintings depict the beauty of Mumbai during monsoon. You would be amazed to find the contrast of different colours in my painting. I am sure that the flow would rethink how beautiful rain and colours can be.
          Choosing rainy season as my theme and not showing how disappointing rainy season can be, I’ve tried to put together my colour’s and bring out mumbai’s rainy in the most fasinating manner.

artwork.name: an afternoon in mumbai
artwork.description:
you will always find & experience a lot of crowdy location’s in my painting’s. as per my opinion and view I always feel a bright enthusiasm & energy in such unknown crowded lanes & location’s in Mumbai. You will always feel & experience yourself & your internal feelings while observing these painting’s which are expressing the common mans real life & hard struggle to earn his livelihood. The roads travelling towards a long way shown in the painting will give you a different feeling’s & thought’s. I have paint so many location’s & spot’s in Mumbai which attracted me just due to their life full attitude.
        The crowdy roads & lanes shown in my painting’s will never allow you to fill lonely & guide your lives towards proper path. I have captured the splashing energy, spirited enthusiasm, hardship of life struggle & a real atmosphere of Mumbai with the free flow of different colours on my canvas. Most people hate to join the mobs & crowds but I say be positive & push yourself in the lively waves of crowds, then only you will experience the touch of real life & creativety.
       All my painting’s gave me the impulse for writing & drawing my mind.

artwork.name: Untitled
artwork.description:
I believe, The most simple is the best and the simplest things are most difficult to create. I am from a small village of Maharashtra State, India and now I am in metro city, so the amalgams of nature and city life are mirrored in my work … As a child I loved visiting rivers and was fascinated by the reflection of shallow water, trees, the textures of wood, stones and leaves. These developed into frames of reference and manifest themselves as windows and boxes in my work… I frequently use geometric shapes, squares and rectangles. It depicts my current urban habitat. In spite of coming from a rural background I cannot deny the effects of urbanization on me. Hence, my works bring out this very blend of urban and rural India.
 As every painting gives me pleasure, so does the medium. Each medium keeps on encouraging me to explore and experiment. All my paintings have given me sublime satisfaction of creation. The feeling of immense joy, which I have experienced, I hope to offer the same to the viewer.

artwork.name: Indian Steam Locomotives 01
artwork.description:
The "Nostalgic" itself always is an emotional memories of our early days of life, which we never forget, which is always being with us. That exciting memories always feel us happy… and make us sentimental…

…Same happened with me. I never forget those memories of my early days. Where, I used to spend time with the locomotives. Day by day I was running to the locomotives. Still now, I remember fun of steams coming out from  engine, I love the sound of whistling “…Choo… Choo… Choo…”

Those were most happiest day in my life… Those memories are always recalled, and influenced me to do the series of canvas on the steam locomotives …

That’s the story behind the TITLE of the show “Nostalgia of Steam Locomotives”.

artwork.name: Indian Steam Locomotives 13
artwork.description:
That time, I was around 5 to 6 years old. I lived in a place where the locomotives travel around. And I was always running out to watch them and I loved to sketch them. This was my old memory of childhood. I try to recall that and translate into the canvas. That is how the series of "NOSTALGIA OF STEAM LOCOMOTIVES" has come up...

Presently there is no Steam Locomotive around us. You might be seen in the museum or other places as antic. My idea is to percent those locomotives to the new generation through this exhibition.

It’s a Nostalgia of YOU & Me…

artwork.description:
My art is not about imitation it is about creation. My process inculcates vivid perspective such as object and its environment. Reciprocated as environment and its objects within. Also objects with its objectives, including object in its literal as well as material sense. Due to which immense forms were derived. Constant interpretation of process got in repetitive forms in my painting. Ultimately making realize that form is utmost vitality for me to paint. Gradually proceeding process made realize that there are some unknown realities beyond obvious realm that has to be explored. Due to which my work keeps changing from very real object’s to the aura which it creates on me.

When an object is observed, after a certain period only its color is seen and then its form is visible. I appreciate the visual in this accept. Space both on canvas as well as in mind equally participates in transforming the objet to the surface. It is about transferring image/object from reality on to the surface, in terms to its pictorial. I constantly experiment with colors, composition, surface and technique. Experience of experimenting gives a new direction to my creative study. Visual treatment, composition and delicate images that emerge through my paintings bear my own unique individuality. 

Now in recent works my total attention is to capture the essence of things through my visual perception. I have deliberately painted colors to get a feel of mysteriousness and to evoke other dimensions of intangible world. Forms provoking me as collective harmony is very essential part for evolution.
 
My painting is an attempt to build a bridge between tangible and intangible realities of existence. I constantly try to improve on what is already being achieved and have a high aim of reaching global art scene, determining struggling towards the limit less horizon of divine creativity.

artwork.name: Non-stop
artwork.description:
Horses always increased the dignity of the ancient kings.
And so even, in today’s modern world, even in most of the republican countries, Horses are used to show the dignity of the government.
According to Hindu Vastu Shastra, picture or sculpture of a horse in the house or office gives the good-luck or good fruits ( progress ) to the owner.

The Horse is very loyal animal. The horse in this sculptures, is coming from long distance and still going ahead till he finds his owner.

artwork.name: Untitled
artwork.description:
Life is a flow. It flows thru time. It flows thru places and spaces. It flows thru emotions and experiences. Most important of all – it flows thru many other lives. Life has ups and downs which are inevitable. It has a natural flow of its own which is asymmetrical and indefinable to conform with. We cannot control everything that comes through our life but we can rejoice different moments if we go by the flow.

My work reflects on this complex and vivid human experience utilizing abstract forms accentuated with figurative motifs.

artwork.name: Ganga Arti at Haridwar
artwork.description: In Haridwar, every evening at dusk, priests perform Ganga "Aarti", that is, offer prayers to the river as the river Ganga is worshipped as Goddess in India. A large number of people gather  on both banks of the river. The priests hold large fire bowls in their hands, their chants fill the air and the gongs in the temples start ringing. People float earthen 'Diyas' (lamps) on the river. The atmosphere is not just visually beautiful, it is also a moving and uplifting experience.

artwork.name: Suryanamaskar at Haridwar
artwork.description: Suryanamaskar, translated means, salutations to the sun. Haridwar in the north of India, is one of the holy cities here. Usually, for the pilgrims, the day begins with a dip in the sacred river Ganges and suryanamaskar.
